---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use — SnapInspect AI"
  description="Terms of Use for the SnapInspect AI iOS app. $99.99/month subscription with 14-day free trial."
  ogPath="/terms"
>
  <section class="border-b border-[var(--color-line-soft)]">
    <div class="container-editorial pt-16 pb-12 md:pt-24 md:pb-16">
      <div class="flex items-center justify-between mb-12">
        <span class="label">№ 008 — Terms of Use</span>
        <span class="label">Effective June 14, 2026</span>
      </div>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8">
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-2">
          <p class="chapter-mark">SECTION</p>
        </div>
        <div class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9">
          <h1 class="font-display text-[clamp(3rem,7vw,6rem)] leading-[0.95]">
            Terms<br/>
            <em class="text-[var(--color-rust)]">of Use.</em>
          </h1>
          <p class="mt-8 text-lg text-[var(--color-ink-soft)] max-w-2xl">
            By downloading or using SnapInspect AI, you agree to these Terms of Use. Please read them carefully.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="py-20">
    <div class="container-editorial">
      <div class="grid grid-cols-12 gap-8">
        <aside class="col-span-12 md:col-span-2 hidden md:block">
          <p class="label mb-4 sticky top-24">CONTENTS</p>
          <ul class="text-xs space-y-2 sticky top-32 text-[var(--color-gray)]">
            <li><a href="#subscription" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rust)]">01 — Subscription</a></li>
            <li><a href="#unlocks" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rust)]">02 — What Unlocks</a></li>
            <li><a href="#use" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rust)]">03 — Acceptable Use</a></li>
            <li><a href="#ai" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rust)]">04 — AI Content</a></li>
            <li><a href="#responsibility" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rust)]">05 — Responsibility</a></li>
            <li><a href="#ip" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rust)]">06 — IP</a></li>
            <li><a href="#warranty" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rust)]">07 — Warranty</a></li>
            <li><a href="#liability" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rust)]">08 — Liability</a></li>
            <li><a href="#changes" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rust)]">09 — Changes</a></li>
            <li><a href="#law" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rust)]">10 — Law</a></li>
            <li><a href="#contact" class="hover:text-[var(--color-rust)]">11 — Contact</a></li>
          </ul>
        </aside>

        <article class="col-span-12 md:col-span-9 md:col-start-3">
          <div class="prose-editorial">
            <h2 id="subscription">1. Subscription Terms</h2>
            <p>SnapInspect Pro is offered as an auto-renewing monthly subscription:</p>
            <ul>
              <li><strong>Price:</strong> $99.99 USD per month</li>
              <li><strong>Free trial:</strong> 14 days for new subscribers. You will not be charged during the trial</li>
              <li><strong>Auto-renewal:</strong> Your subscription will automatically renew at the end of each monthly period unless cancelled at least 24 hours before the end of the current period</li>
              <li><strong>Billing:</strong> Payment is charged to your Apple ID at confirmation of purchase</li>
              <li><strong>Managing your subscription:</strong> Open iPhone Settings → your name → Subscriptions → SnapInspect AI. You can cancel any time</li>
              <li><strong>Refunds:</strong> Refunds are handled by Apple according to <a href="https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT204084">Apple's refund policy</a></li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="unlocks">2. What the Subscription Unlocks</h2>
            <p>An active SnapInspect Pro subscription unlocks:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>AI Polish on findings</li>
              <li>AI-generated client and inspector summaries</li>
              <li>Professional PDF report generation</li>
            </ul>
            <p>Without an active subscription, you can still create inspections, take photos, and capture notes, but the AI and report-generation features are locked.</p>

            <h2 id="use">3. Acceptable Use</h2>
            <p>You agree not to:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Use the app for any illegal purpose</li>
              <li>Attempt to reverse engineer, decompile, or modify the app</li>
              <li>Use the app to generate or distribute false, misleading, or fraudulent inspection reports</li>
              <li>Abuse, overload, or attack our backend services</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="ai">4. AI-Generated Content</h2>
            <p>The app uses Anthropic's Claude AI to generate report language and summaries based on your notes. AI-generated content may contain inaccuracies. <strong>You are responsible for reviewing and verifying all AI-generated content before delivering inspection reports to clients.</strong> SnapInspect AI is a writing assistant — not a substitute for professional inspector judgment.</p>

            <h2 id="responsibility">5. Professional Responsibility</h2>
            <p>SnapInspect AI is a documentation tool for licensed home inspectors. You are solely responsible for:</p>
            <ul>
              <li>Conducting accurate, professional inspections in accordance with applicable standards and laws</li>
              <li>The accuracy and completeness of any reports you generate or deliver</li>
              <li>Compliance with all licensing, insurance, and regulatory requirements in your jurisdiction</li>
            </ul>

            <h2 id="ip">6. Intellectual Property</h2>
            <p>The app, its code, design, and content are owned by Gregory Voetsch. You retain ownership of the inspection data, photos, and reports you create with the app.</p>

            <h2 id="warranty">7. Disclaimer of Warranties</h2>
            <p>THE APP IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED, INCLUDING WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE, AND NON-INFRINGEMENT.</p>

            <h2 id="liability">8. Limitation of Liability</h2>
            <p>TO THE MAXIMUM EXTENT PERMITTED BY LAW, IN NO EVENT WILL SNAPINSPECT AI OR ITS DEVELOPER BE LIABLE FOR ANY INDIRECT, INCIDENTAL, SPECIAL, CONSEQUENTIAL, OR PUNITIVE DAMAGES ARISING OUT OF OR RELATED TO YOUR USE OF THE APP, INCLUDING WITHOUT LIMITATION DAMAGES FOR LOSS OF DATA, BUSINESS INTERRUPTION, OR LOSS OF PROFITS. OUR TOTAL LIABILITY WILL NOT EXCEED THE AMOUNT YOU PAID FOR THE SUBSCRIPTION IN THE PRECEDING 12 MONTHS.</p>

            <h2 id="changes">9. Changes to These Terms</h2>
            <p>We may update these Terms from time to time. The "Effective date" above will reflect when changes were made. Continued use of the app after changes constitutes acceptance.</p>

            <h2 id="law">10. Governing Law</h2>
            <p>These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Florida, United States, without regard to its conflict of laws principles.</p>

            <h2 id="contact">11. Contact</h2>
            <p>Questions about these Terms? Email <a href="mailto:gregg.voetsch@gmail.com">gregg.voetsch@gmail.com</a>.</p>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
